Gossaert. Ad [Addendum] Grimani Breviary: T. [Tullia] Gasparini [Leporace], Il Calendario del Breviario Grimani, Milano, 1954; Sforza Hours (Add. MS 34294): At the direction of Margaret of Austria Horenbout painted 16 miniatures & 2 borders in this late 15th century Milanese MS (Hours of Bona Maria Sforza, widow of Galeazzo Maria Sforza) which was in Margaret's collection, 2 of the Flemish additions are dated, one 1579, the other 1520. Hulin (Annuaire des Musées & des Beaux-Arts II, 1939, pp. 16-18, assigned the addiditions to Gerard Horenbout; Motifs used by Bruegel: 1) Falling snow in December picture of Vienna MS 2706 (Hortulus Animae, c. 1510-1520) by Dornhöffer in 2 vols. 1907-11; 2) choppy sea in February Munich cod. lat. 23638 (Book of Hours, early XVI, Simon Bening) see G. [Georg] Leidinger, Miniaturen aus Handschriften der Kgl. Hof- und Staatsbibliothek in München 1912; 3) [onleesbaar] in February Grimani Breviary [scan].
